an alternative model to traditional research practice, one where community members “share authority” as equal partners in a project. More than a hundred photographs illustrate the experiences of those who participated in the project and highlight the intersections between oral history, digital media, and performance. A sustained reflection on collaborative research, Oral History at the Crossroads has methodological and ethical implications for scholars. And, as a contemporary model for curating oral and public history, it pushes the field in new directions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aOral historyzQuébec (Province)zMontréal. 0aOral historyzQuébec (Province)zMontréal. 0aPublic historyzQuébec (Province)zMontréal. 0aPublic historyzQuébec (Province)zMontréal. 0aRefugeeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aRefugeeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvInterviews. 0aRefugeeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aRefugeeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aRefugeeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvInterviews. 0aRefugeeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aSurvivalxHistory. 0aViolencexHistory. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh1 aHigh, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZembrzycki, Stacey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311141999240uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482685340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774826853423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774826853/o